PREHEAT oven to 425 degrees F. PLACE Homestyle Beef and water in 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate; cover and microwave on high for 3 minutes; stir, re-cover, and continue cooking on high for 3 minutes. Sprinkle with pepper to taste. TOP with pie crust; fold edges under and crimp. Cut four slits towards center of crust. BAKE for 18-20 minutes or until crust is golden brown. SEASON with ground black pepper.